/**
 * Spawn Context Builder — Asolaria's Internal Agent Briefing System
 *
 * When Asolaria spawns a real agent inside the black hole, she needs to
 * decide WHAT that agent knows. This module is her PID controller:
 *
 *   P (Proportional) — current blockers, health state, active alarms
 *   I (Integral)     — accumulated LX knowledge, filtered by agent role
 *   D (Derivative)   — recent MQTT traffic, inbox delta, drift signals
 *
 * Each agent role gets a compressed, role-specific briefing — not the
 * full index. The spawn-PID is virtual (role + timestamp), not an OS PID.
 *
 * Flow:
 *   Asolaria wakes → searches LX index (I) → checks health (P) →
 *   checks drift signals (D) → buildSpawnContext("helm") → markdown packet →
 *   real Helm spawns with ONLY what he needs → identity handshake →
 *   Helm works → despawns → indexes what he learned → next spawn updated
 *
 * LX chain: LX-122 (identity handshake), LX-116 (awakening), LX-111 (swarm collapse)
 */

